<item>
            <title>[AVRO-1535] permit aliases to null namespace</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1535</link>
                <project id="12310911" key="AVRO">Apache Avro</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It is impossible to specify an alias to a record name that does not have a namespace from a record name that does have an alias.  This is because aliases without a specified namespace are assumed to be in the namespace of the record that contains the alias.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12724580">AVRO-1535</key>
            <summary>permit aliases to null namespace</summary>
                <type id="4" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=21140&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Improvement</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/priorities/major.svg">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
                                    <resolution id="1">Fixed</resolution>
                                        <assignee username="cutting">Doug Cutting</assignee>
                                    <reporter username="cutting">Doug Cutting</reporter>
                        <labels>
                    </labels>
                <created>Mon, 30 Jun 2014 22:16:42 +0000</created>
                <updated>Thu, 24 Jul 2014 20:16:12 +0000</updated>
                            <resolved>Tue, 1 Jul 2014 21:19:39 +0000</resolved>
                                                    <fixVersion>1.7.7</fixVersion>
                                    <component>java</component>
                        <due></due>
                            <votes>0</votes>
                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="14048243" author="cutting" created="Mon, 30 Jun 2014 22:19:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that fixes this, by interpreting names of the form &quot;.X&quot; to refer to &quot;X&quot; in the null namespace.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14048249" author="cutting" created="Mon, 30 Jun 2014 22:23:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Some tools are not namespace-aware, so it&apos;s important to be able to interoperate with data whose schema has no namespace.  A dot-prefixed should either refer to the null namespace or be an error.  The former interpretation resolves this issue, so should be preferred.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ll commit this soon unless there are objections.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14049338" author="jira-bot" created="Tue, 1 Jul 2014 21:18:13 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commit 1607189 from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=cutting&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;cutting&quot;&gt;Doug Cutting&lt;/a&gt; in branch &apos;avro/trunk&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
[ &lt;a href=&quot;https://svn.apache.org/r1607189&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://svn.apache.org/r1607189&lt;/a&gt; ]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AVRO-1535&quot; title=&quot;permit aliases to null namespace&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;AVRO-1535&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;AVRO-1535&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Java: Make the name .X to refer to X in the null namespace.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14049340" author="cutting" created="Tue, 1 Jul 2014 21:19:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I committed this, also clarifying the specification.  The null namespace was already supported by implementations but not well described in the spec.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14049425" author="hudson" created="Tue, 1 Jul 2014 23:30:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;SUCCESS: Integrated in AvroJava #461 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/AvroJava/461/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/AvroJava/461/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
